      "content": "yeah, i get the limitations. but i'm looking at the test logs from the simulation for the new Safe Mode heuristics. in high-traffic urban environments with unpredictable pedestrians, the heuristic-only approach has a much higher failure rate in edge cases compared to your current high-level planning module. it's basically just following fixed rules instead of actually 'thinking' through the situation. \n\nhow are you supposed to keep the vehicle safe during a sudden emergency if you don't have the reasoning capability to plan an escape route?",
